This paper discusses the representation of word senses and concepts, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to create these representations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for these representations to improve performance in natural language processing applications, which is a common goal in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the application of these models to other linguistic items, such as phrases and sentences, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
